data.title: Jean-Louis Murat: the singer died at the age of 71 years
data.meta_description: Both author, composer and performer, the artist Jean-Louis Murat died this Thursday, May 25, 2023. He was 71 years old.
data.text:
Jean-Louis Murat, whose real name is Jean-Louis Bergheaud, died this Thursday, May 25, 2023, at the age of 71 years. This was announced by his manager to our colleagues of France Inter.

At the head of a score of records published since the early 80s, the author, composer and performer French, born in 1952 in Chamalières in the Puy-de-Dôme, began his career in a rock band in the late 1970s. Spotted by William Sheller, the group then provides the first parts of his concerts.

Jean-Louis Murat quickly pursued his solo career and had his first success in 1987 with the release of the song " Si je devais manquer de toi ". Then followed the songs " L'Ange déchu " and " Te garder près de moi ", taken from the album"Cheyenne Autumn", released in 1989.

But it is especially the song " Regrets ", in duet with Mylène Farmer, which allows him to be really known in 1991.

Many people then discovered the poetry of Jean-Louis Murat 's lyrics and his extreme sensitivity, which will never leave him.

If the artist is prolific for his own discography, he is also prolific for others. Jean-Louis Murat had written for other artists, such as Françoise Hardy and Isabelle Boulay or for Indochine, on the hit " Un singe en hiver " and the single " Karma girls ".
